t moment: the young woman laughs in front of her new car, while the suited man clenches his fists and gestures angrily beside the stripped sedan.\n\nThe story then moves into a State Farm office. Through glass doors, the tall man and the young woman enter or stand near the entrance while the suited man passes inside. A red rectangular sign on the right reads “StateFarm” in white letters and shows the company’s three-circle logo. Small white legal text appears along the bottom of the screen. The suited man walks forward inside the bright office lobby, looking worn out but composed. Large white on-screen text appears over him reading “Car Insurance,” with the State Farm sign still visible beside him.\n\nOutside the State Farm office, the tall man and young woman come out through the glass doors and down the steps together. The storefront has large windows, metal railings, and another red State Farm sign visible through the glass. Large white text now reads “Car Loans.” The pair smile and walk side by side; the man places an arm around the young woman’s shoulders, and she moves with a light, happy bounce, still wearing the pink hoodie and sunrise T-shirt. A red graphic wash begins to cover the scene, and the words “Here to” appear alongside the “Car Loans” text. The commercial ends on a full red screen with white text reading “Here to help,” with small fine print along the bottom.",
